  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of life-saving primary and secondary healthcare services for the most vulnerable communities living in the refugees settlements with a focus on Adjumani, Arua, Isingiro, Kikuube, Kyegegwa, Lamwo; and Moyo districts</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to strengthen the detection and response to epidemics in the refugee hosting districts.  WFP will use CERF funds to orient Village Health Teams on Community Based disease Surveillance, deploy an Emergency Rapid Response Team during outbreaks and procure outbreak investigation kits among other activities.  1,022,491 refugees and people in host communities will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within 9 months.</narrative>
  </description>
